They execute automatically before your type's first use.
( Not to be confused with instance initialization blocks, which execute before any constructors )

In contrast, static initialization blocks execute before you even start using the Type. 
We can think of these as "Type initializers"

Statements are enclosed in braces, outside of any methods or constructors. Precede with static keyword.

Cannot access any instance members - can only access static members.

must handle all checked exceptions